<subSubSection pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,1634,2021]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,420,1634,1661]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<typeStatus box="[151,269,1635,1661]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Lectotype</typeStatus>
designation.
</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Malaise, R." box="[427,597,1635,1661]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 68" refId="ref74904" refString="Malaise, R. (1931) Entomologische Ergebnisse der schwedischen Kamtchatka Expedition 1920 - 1922. (35. Tenthredinidae). Arkiv for Zoologi, 23 (2 [A 8]), 1 - 68." type="journal article" year="1931">Malaise (1931)</bibRefCitation>
described this species based on “ 
<specimenCount box="[970,1028,1635,1661]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="male">2♂♂</specimenCount>
und 
<specimenCount box="[1083,1140,1635,1661]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="female">2♀♀</specimenCount>
aus Klutchi, 
<collectingRegion box="[1289,1427,1635,1661]" country="Russia" name="Kamchatka" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Kamtchatka</collectingRegion>
” but did not designate a 
<typeStatus box="[412,514,1671,1697]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">holotype</typeStatus>
. We hereby designate the female labeled “Typus” in Malaise’s collection (NHRS), as 
<typeStatus box="[181,287,1707,1733]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">lectotype</typeStatus>
. It is labeled “ 
<collectingRegion box="[441,593,1707,1733]" country="Russia" name="Kamchatka" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Kamtschatka</collectingRegion>
, Malaise” “Typus” “ 
<taxonomicName authority="Mal." authorityName="Malaise" authorityYear="1931" box="[820,1117,1707,1733]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virescens">Pamphilius virescens Mal.</taxonomicName>
Type Malaise det.” “818”. It was treated as the 
<typeStatus box="[356,454,1743,1769]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">holotype</typeStatus>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Benes, K." box="[496,646,1743,1769]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="298 - 314" refId="ref72854" refString="Benes, K. (1974) The Siberian species of Pamphilius Latr., related to P. histrio Latr. (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae). Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca, 71, 298 - 314." type="journal article" year="1974">Beneš (1974)</bibRefCitation>
and Shinohara (1995) and fully redescribed by 
<bibRefCitation author="Benes, K." box="[1182,1335,1743,1769]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="298 - 314" refId="ref72854" refString="Benes, K. (1974) The Siberian species of Pamphilius Latr., related to P. histrio Latr. (Hymenoptera, Pamphiliidae). Acta Entomologica Bohemoslovaca, 71, 298 - 314." type="journal article" year="1974">Beneš (1974)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
