<subSubSection lastPageId="73" lastPageNumber="74" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="72.[151,1437,1634,2021]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1959,1985]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">Remarks</emphasis>
. This species is known from a small number of specimens (Shinohara 1995) and no molecular data are available. It belongs to the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Dahlbom" baseAuthorityYear="1835" box="[502,643,1995,2021]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gyllenhali">
<emphasis box="[502,643,1995,2021]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">P. gyllenhali</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup of the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Latreille" authorityYear="1812" box="[837,939,1995,2021]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="histrio">
<emphasis box="[837,939,1995,2021]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">P. histrio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group (
<bibRefCitation author="Shinohara, A." box="[1028,1226,1995,2021]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="359 - 438" refId="ref76809" refString="Shinohara, A. (2002 b) Systematics of the leaf-rolling or webspinning sawfly subfamily Pamphiliinae: a preliminary overview. In: Viitasaari, M. (Ed.), Sawflies (Hymenoptera, Symphyta) I. Tremex Press, Helsinki, pp. 359 - 438." type="book chapter" year="2002">Shinohara 2002b</bibRefCitation>
). 
<bibRefCitation author="Lee, J. - W. &amp; Choi, J. - K. &amp; Park, B." box="[1246,1436,1995,2021]" pageId="72" pageNumber="73" pagination="1 - 96" refId="ref74711" refString="Lee, J. - W., Choi, J. - K. &amp; Park, B. (2019) Synoptic list of Symphyta (Hymenoptera) in Korea. Journal of Species Research, 8, 1 - 96." type="journal article" year="2019">
Lee 
<emphasis box="[1296,1354,1995,2021]" italics="true" pageId="72" pageNumber="73">et al.</emphasis>
(2019)
</bibRefCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="73.[151,1436,151,249]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">
gave 
<taxonomicName box="[210,304,151,177]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[210,266,151,177]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Salix</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
as a host of this species without showing the source of information. 
<bibRefCitation author="Verzhutskij, B. N." box="[1056,1264,151,177]" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" pagination="1 - 162" refId="ref80514" refString="Verzhutskij, B. N. (1966) Pilil'shchiki Pribajkal'ja. Nauka, Moskva, pp. 1 - 162." type="book chapter" year="1966">Verzhutskij (1966)</bibRefCitation>
speculated that the host of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Malaise" authorityYear="1931" box="[273,402,187,212]" class="Insecta" family="Pamphiliidae" genus="Pamphilius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virescens">
<emphasis box="[273,402,187,212]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">P. virescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was 
<taxonomicName box="[458,514,187,213]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Salix" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="73" pageNumber="74" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[458,514,187,213]" italics="true" pageId="73" pageNumber="74">Salix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. As discussed by Shinohara (1995), this host record may be correct, but no decisive evidence is available.
</paragraph>
